Description: SmoothNAS storage management daemon
 tierd is the SmoothNAS control-plane daemon. It owns the pool,
 tier, share, and movement state machines that sit above smoothfs
 and the protocol exports (NFS, SMB, iSCSI). Talks to the smoothfs
 kernel module over generic netlink, persists control-plane state
 in SQLite, and exposes a REST API + `tierd-cli` for operators and
 upper-layer tooling.
 .
 This package ships the tierd daemon, the tierd-cli operator CLI,
 and systemd units for the long-lived control plane plus one-shot
 host initialization before tierd starts. smoothfs-dkms and
 smoothfs-samba-vfs are Recommends rather than Depends: tierd runs
 (degraded) on hosts without smoothfs installed — useful for day-one
 appliance provisioning where tier pools haven't been created yet.
